at%20Google%20in%20the%20US%20unsustainable%2C%20so%20she%20quit%20and%20traveled%20with%20her%20partner%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20watercolor%20hobby%20she%20picked%20up%20on%20a%20Thai%20island%20turned%20into%20a%20new%20career%2C%20leading%20her%20to%20open%20an%20art%20studio%20in%20San%20Diego.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sara%20Wilczynska%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Swil%20Arts%20Studio.%20She%20left%20her%20job%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google%2C%20spent%20a%20year%20traveling%20with%20her%20partner%2C%20and%20discovered%20watercolors%20in%20Thailand.%20Her%20words%20have%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Warsaw%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20Poland%20was%20still%20a%20communist%20country.%20I%20remember%20witnessing%20the%20shift%20into%20capitalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20earned%20a%20master's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freason-incoming-freshman-wants-computer-science-degree-despite-ai-fears-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edegree%20in%20computer%20science%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Warsaw%2C%20interning%20in%20Barcelona%20and%20studying%20abroad%20in%20Edinburgh%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2025%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20London%20to%20work%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20an%20investment%20bank.%20I%20stayed%20nearly%20five%20years%2C%20but%20even%20then%2C%20there%20was%20a%20quiet%20voice%20in%20the%20background%20asking%20whether%20this%20was%20really%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfc5f819-2351-49fb-b46c-eef863bc1ffa%5C%22%3EI%20started%20working%20at%20Google%20in%202015%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Google%20in%20Zurich%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20step%20closer%20to%20something%20more%20meaningful.%20After%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20I%20got%20my%20US%20visa%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-new-york-city-different-than-visiting-lessons-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransferred%20to%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20news%20section%20of%20the%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20my%20career%20was%20everything%20I%20had%20worked%20toward.%20Google%20was%20flexible%2C%20supportive%2C%20and%20full%20of%20brilliant%20people.%20I%20had%20autonomy%20over%20my%20work%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20projects%20to%20my%20physical%20working%20location%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-loyalty-corporate-america-dysfunction-employers-employees-att-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebenefits%20were%20incredible%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20standing%20with%20New%20York%20City%20in%20the%20Background.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45de6a2680585ce91a3750%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223036%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20she%20got%20her%20US%20visa%2C%20she%20was%20transferred%20to%20New%20York%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20days%20included%20coding%2C%20meetings%2C%20but%20also%20yoga%20classes%2C%20gym%20sessions%2C%20gourmet%20birthday%20meals%2C%20and%20even%20subsidized%20massages.%20There%20was%20also%20stability%20%E2%80%94%20a%20good%20paycheck%20and%20stock%20grant%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20also%20what%20made%20it%20so%20hard%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20as%20my%20career%20progressed%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20promoted%20twice%20within%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20there%20was%20more%20high-level%20work%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20stakeholder%20meetings%2C%20and%20less%20hands-on%20coding%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20feel%20disconnected.%20A%20growing%20sense%20that%20the%20pace%20wasn't%20sustainable%20for%20me.%20That%20constant%20stimulation%20%E2%80%94%20screens%2C%20deadlines%2C%20notifications%2C%20expectations%20%E2%80%94%20was%20pulling%20me%20away%20from%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20later%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20San%20Diego%20with%20my%20partner%2C%20Valentina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2284c228e8-d7e6-427e-8763-b36f2ab58e83%5C%22%3ESomething%20shifted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flived-in-different-cities-to-find-dream-home-san-diego-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20San%20Diego%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20forced%20me%20to%20slow%20down.%20There%20was%20nature%20everywhere%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ocean%2C%20the%20desert%2C%20the%20mountains%20%E2%80%94%20and%20suddenly%20I%20had%20space%20to%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20noticing%20small%20things%20again.%20The%20scent%20of%20jasmine%20on%20a%20warm%20evening.%20The%20simple%20joy%20of%20eating%20a%20fish%20taco.%20That%20realization%20made%20it%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20the%20misalignment%20in%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20fix%20it%20without%20leaving.%20I%20trained%20in%20sound%20healing%20and%20hosted%20sessions.%20I%20took%20on%20different%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-project-eat-ai-infrastructure-tools-chips-artificial-intelligence-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprojects%20at%20Google%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20leading%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives.%20I%20even%20reduced%20my%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20it%20fully%20addressed%20the%20core%20feeling.%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20just%20being%20too%20picky%3F%20Am%20I%20asking%20for%20too%20much%3F%26quot%3B%20Because%20there%20was%20nothing%20objectively%20wrong%20with%20my%20job.%20It%20wasn't%20toxic.%20I%20respected%20my%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20a%20job%20can%20tick%20every%20box%20%E2%80%94%20it%20can%20look%20perfect%20on%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20something%20deeper%20is%20missing%2C%20it's%20not%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20leaving%20wasn't%20easy.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20was%20not%20knowing%20what%20would%20come%20next.%20I%20kept%20thinking%20I%20needed%20a%20plan.%20A%20clear%2C%20logical%20next%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20eventually%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20waiting%20for%20certainty%20was%20just%20keeping%20me%20stuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20made%20a%20decision%20that%20felt%20radical%20at%20the%20time.%20I%20quit%20my%20job%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%20%E2%80%94%20Valentina's%20job%20had%20been%20eliminated%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadult-gap-year-quit-job-travel-the-world-career-pivot-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etravel%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%20We%20rented%20out%20our%20apartment%20in%20San%20Diego%20and%20went%20traveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20standing%20by%20the%20sea%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45dfc6ec11c5f7e7fa7733%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20couple%20left%20San%20Diego%20and%20traveled%20for%20a%20year.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292bc563b-549a-4704-b674-ebe867f70c64%5C%22%3EThat%20year%20changed%20everything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spent%20most%20of%202023%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20with%20shorter%20trips%20to%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20At%20first%2C%20we%20moved%20quickly%2C%20but%20eventually%20we%20slowed%20down.%20We%20spent%20six%20months%20in%20Koh%20Tao%2C%20a%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkoh-samui-thailand-expat-life-ab